2. Magna eloquentia. This is the passage in connexion with which William Pitt is recorded to have proved his ready skill at off-hand translation. Some one having pronounced it untranslateable, he came out with the following : ‘ It is with eloquence as with a flame. It requires fuel to seed it, motion to excite it, and it brightens as it burns ' (Stanhope's Life of Pitt, vol. iii. p. 413). Cp. Cic.
